BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:Meetup: Let's Walk!!
UID:event_314146953@meetup.com
SEQUENCE:1
DTSTAMP:20260410T030758Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260410T093000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260410T113000
SUMMARY:🥾 Let's Hike!! the Turtle Back Trail loop
DESCRIPTION:Let's Walk!!\nCome walk 2 or 4 miles along woods trails in Sou
 th Mountain Reservation near the Turtle Back Rock. We'll take parts of the
  Hillspur and Turtle Back trails to make 2 custom loops. Stay for one or b
 oth 😁.\n\nThese trails are gentle\, **but are not for beginners**. If y
 ou've walked with us at Eagle Rock\, this is similar in difficulty. There 
 may be wet or muddy sections and lots of rocks and tree roots. Please wear
  hiking boots/shoes and bring trekking poles or a walking stick.\n\nDon't 
 forget your water!\n\nInclement weather may cancel this event. Please chec
 k the event page for comments prior to leaving for the meetup.\n\n**Please
  arrive 5 minutes early so we can start on time.**\n\n**Disclaimer:** If y
 ou join this event\, please understand that you are responsible for your o
 wn preparedness and well-being and will hold no one else liable in case of
  injury or mishap.
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.meetup.com/lets-walkprogram/events/314146953/
STATUS:CONFIRMED
CREATED:20260406T133220Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260406T133220Z
CLASS:PUBLIC
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:Meetup: Let's Walk!!
UID:event_314152686@meetup.com
SEQUENCE:1
DTSTAMP:20260410T030758Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260411T100000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260411T113000
SUMMARY:Let's Walk!! Brookdale Park
DESCRIPTION:Let's Walk!!\nIf entering from Bellevue Avenue and park in the
  first parking lot on the left. We will be gathering near the the playgrou
 nd area.\n\nif entering from Watchung Ave\, park and walk up to the upper 
 parking lot near the playground area.\n\nWe will be walking the outer path
 . There are several break-off points if you do not want to walk the entire
  path.\n\nThe walk will be about an hour or at least 3-4 miles.\n\nWear co
 mfortable shoes!\n\nPlease plan to arrive 5 minutes early. The walk will s
 tart promptly.\n\nBrookdale Park offers the public access to both passive 
 and active recreational activities as well as picturesque vistas. Trails f
 or walking and running\, lush groves and extensive lawns\, playgrounds\, s
 ports fields\, track facilities\, tennis courts\, an archery range and sta
 dium grandstand are just some of the numerous attractions that make Brookd
 ale Park a magnet for nature lovers\, families\, and physical fitness enth
 usiasts for miles around.\n\nhttps://www.essexcountyparks.org/parks/brookd
 ale-park\n\nDisclaimer: If you join us for a hike\, please understand that
  you are responsible for your own preparedness and well-being and will hol
 d no one else liable in case of injury or mishap.
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.meetup.com/lets-walkprogram/events/314152686/
STATUS:CONFIRMED
CREATED:20260406T193907Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260406T193907Z
CLASS:PUBLIC
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:Meetup: Let's Walk!!
UID:event_313394384@meetup.com
SEQUENCE:1
DTSTAMP:20260410T030758Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260417T091500
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260417T101500
SUMMARY:Eagle Rock Reservation
DESCRIPTION:Let's Walk!!\nJOIN US FOR A WALK. WE WALK AT A MODERATE PACE O
 N UNPAVED PATHS.\n\nWe will hike for about an hour - 3.5 miles. We will be
  walking on trails in the woods\, so appropriate footwear\, long pants & s
 ocks\, and bug spray.\n\nWill will meet at:\n[https://goo.gl/maps/7rRRTiXC
 ntdE1neD7](https://goo.gl/maps/7rRRTiXCntdE1neD7) Eagle Rock Trail Parking
  Lot by Kiosk#1\n\nIf you enter from Eagle Rock Way\, go pass the Highlawn
  and stay left. There will be a parking lot at the end of the curve to you
 r right.\n\nEagle Rock Reservation is 408 acres of hills\, streams\, and v
 alleys located on the borders of West Orange\, Verona\, and Montclair\, Ne
 w Jersey. Though located in the middle of the most densely populated count
 y in the most densely populated state in the country\, the Reservation is 
 mostly undeveloped and boasts an extensive trail system within its borders
 .\n\n**Please make sure to RSVP and arrive 5 minutes prior to start time.*
 *\n\nFOLLOW US ON INSTAGRAM - letswalkmeetup\n\nDisclaimer: If you join us
  for a hike\, please understand that you are responsible for your own prep
 aredness and well-being and will hold no one else liable in case of injury
  or mishap. Event will be canceled in the event of extreme weather.
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.meetup.com/lets-walkprogram/events/313394384/
STATUS:CONFIRMED
CREATED:20260217T063238Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260217T063238Z
CLASS:PUBLIC
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:Meetup: Let's Walk!!
UID:event_314039666@meetup.com
SEQUENCE:1
DTSTAMP:20260410T030758Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260422T091500
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260422T101500
SUMMARY:🌎EARTH DAY clean up at Eagle Rock Reservation
DESCRIPTION:Let's Walk!!\n**This is a special event for Earth Day 2026. We
  will be collecting trash along our usual hiking route. Trash bags and dis
 posable gloves will be provided**\n\nWe will hike for about an hour - 3.5 
 miles. We will be walking on trails in the woods\, so appropriate footwear
 \, long pants & socks\, and bug spray.\n\nWill will meet at:\n[https://goo
 .gl/maps/7rRRTiXCntdE1neD7](https://goo.gl/maps/7rRRTiXCntdE1neD7) Eagle R
 ock Trail Parking Lot by Kiosk#1\n\nIf you enter from Eagle Rock Way\, go 
 pass the Highlawn and stay left. There will be a parking lot at the end of
  the curve to your right.\n\nEagle Rock Reservation is 408 acres of hills\
 , streams\, and valleys located on the borders of West Orange\, Verona\, a
 nd Montclair\, New Jersey. Though located in the middle of the most densel
 y populated county in the most densely populated state in the country\, th
 e Reservation is mostly undeveloped and boasts an extensive trail system w
 ithin its borders.\n\n**Please make sure to RSVP and arrive 5 minutes prio
 r to start time.**\n\nFOLLOW US ON INSTAGRAM - letswalkmeetup\n\nDisclaime
 r: If you join us for a hike\, please understand that you are responsible 
 for your own preparedness and well-being and will hold no one else liable 
 in case of injury or mishap. Event will be canceled in the event of extrem
 e weather.
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.meetup.com/lets-walkprogram/events/314039666/
STATUS:CONFIRMED
CREATED:20260330T161841Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260330T161841Z
CLASS:PUBLIC
END:VEVENT
